1. this always points to a current object.

2. this is a reference variable which holds the refernce id of current object.

3. Whenever class level variable and a local variable both are having same name then this concept is known as data shadowing.

4. Priority always goes to a local variable.

5. You can not access instance data members of class without using refernce id dot.

6. this keyword can not be used in any static function.

7. If you are passing "this" as argument in any instance function of a class then it must be the first argument.